<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1934-04-30T15:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1934-04-30T15:00:00-05:00" n="438" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d438">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">721.23/2241: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                the Minister in Switzerland</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Wilson</hi></persName>), <hi rend="italic">at
                                Geneva</hi></head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1934-04-30T16:00:00-04:00">April 30, 1934—4
                                p.m.</date></dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>143. Your 236, April 26, noon. Our information from Bogotá, Lima and Rio
                            de Janeiro appears to warrant optimism as to the possibility of direct
                            settlement between Colombia and Perú in the present negotiations.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>